# Observation-forecast smoother, using OpenCV-library
# jussi.ylhaisi@fmi.fi
# tuuli.perttula@fmi.fi

# Input is obs field (one timestep, forecast hour 0) and forecast field (x timesteps, up until forecast hour x-1). Output is interpolated forecast field (x timesteps, up until forecast hour x-1). The first timestep of the model data is the same as used for the analysis field. -> e.g. The example fcst dataset in testdata/testdata_nwc_230700/ has a time length of 6 but forecasts ranging only up until forecast hour 5.



# EXAMPLE RUNS
# python call_interpolation.py --obsdata testdata/obsdata_nomissing.grib2 --modeldata testdata/modeldata_nomissing.grib2 --interpolated_data outdata/interp.grib2
wrote file 'outdata/interp.grib2'
